      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZIPPING KRAVITZ (8) hit the ground running from an outside draw with a fast early split, holding on for a minor placing when third and beaten 3.5 lengths at this track over 520m in 30.16. Deserves serious consideration. MALICIOUS (7) failed to feature last start after missing the jump at this track, but prior to that won by a neck at this track (29.79) beating Malawi Rebel in a OPEN on March 12. Should be about the money. COCHISE ATTITUDE (4) stalked the lead after a clean break from the tricky draw and went on to finish second (29.86) at this track in a Grade 5 over 520m. Has a very good strike-rate from this draw, with five wins from eight starts. Expecting another good run. HARA'S MILLY (3) was well supported last time but could only manage third (25.78), beaten 7 lengths. Was a winner at her only start from this draw. Well placed and gets her chance.",
